In[3]:
# 2. Extract and save PNGs from TFRecords
feature_desc = {
    "label_normal": tf.io.FixedLenFeature([], tf.int64),
    "image":        tf.io.FixedLenFeature([], tf.string),
}

idx = 0
for shard in SHARDS:
    ds = tf.data.TFRecordDataset(shard)
    for raw in ds:
        ex = tf.io.parse_single_example(raw, feature_desc)
        flat = tf.io.decode_raw(ex["image"], tf.uint8)    # uint8 [0..255]
        img_np = flat.numpy().reshape(299, 299)           # back to 2D

        #  CHANGE HERE: single CV2 resize + convert to RGB, no tf.image.resize, no *255 wrap
        resized = cv2.resize(img_np, IMG_SIZE, interpolation=cv2.INTER_AREA)
        rgb     = cv2.cvtColor(resized, cv2.COLOR_GRAY2RGB)  # shape (224,224,3), uint8

        label = int(ex["label_normal"].numpy())
        fname = OUTPUT_DIR / str(label) / f"img_{idx:06d}.png"
        cv2.imwrite(str(fname), rgb)
        idx += 1

gc.collect()

# 5. Helper loaders
def _read_resized(p, size=IMG_SIZE):
    im = cv2.imread(p, cv2.IMREAD_COLOR)
    return cv2.resize(im, size, interpolation=cv2.INTER_AREA)

def _load_block(plist):
    arr = np.empty((len(plist), *IMG_SIZE, 3), dtype=np.uint8)
    for i, p in enumerate(plist):
        arr[i] = _read_resized(p)
    return arr

In[13]:
inputs = Input(shape=(224, 224, 3), name="input_rgb")

x = Lambda(preprocess_input, name="resnet_preproc")(inputs)

backbone = ResNet50(include_top=False,
                    weights="imagenet",
                    input_tensor=x)

for layer in backbone.layers:       
    layer.trainable = False        

x   = GlobalAveragePooling2D()(backbone.output)
x   = Dropout(0.50)(x)
x   = Dense(256, activation="relu")(x)        
x   = Dropout(0.25)(x)
out = Dense(1, activation="sigmoid", name="pred")(x) 

model = Model(inputs, out, name="resnet50_baseline")

from tensorflow.keras.callbacks import (ModelCheckpoint,
                                        ReduceLROnPlateau,
                                        EarlyStopping, Callback)
weight_path = "mammography_resnet.best.h5"

checkpoint = ModelCheckpoint(filepath=weight_path,
                             monitor='val_auc',
                             save_best_only=True,
                             save_weights_only=False,
                             mode='max', verbose=1)

reduce_lr = ReduceLROnPlateau(monitor='val_auc',
                              factor=0.3,
                              patience=3)

early_stop = EarlyStopping(monitor='val_auc',
                           patience=5,
                           mode='max',
                           restore_best_weights=True,
                           verbose=1)

callbacks_list = [checkpoint, early_stop, reduce_lr]

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import numpy as np

def plot_learning_curves(hist, save_as="mammography_resnet_learning.png"):
    acc      = hist.get('accuracy',  hist.get('acc'))
    val_acc  = hist.get('val_accuracy', hist.get('val_acc'))
    loss     = hist['loss']
    val_loss = hist['val_loss']

    epochs = range(1, len(acc) + 1)
    fig, (ax1, ax2) = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=(18, 7))
    fig.suptitle("Mammography ResNet50 Baseline  Training Progress")

    ax1.plot(epochs, acc,      label='Train Acc')
    ax1.plot(epochs, val_acc,  label='Val Acc')
    ax1.set_xlabel('Epoch'); ax1.set_ylabel('Accuracy')
    ax1.legend(); ax1.grid(True)

    ax2.plot(epochs, loss,     label='Train Loss')
    ax2.plot(epochs, val_loss, label='Val Loss')
    ax2.set_xlabel('Epoch'); ax2.set_ylabel('Binary-CE Loss')
    ax2.legend(); ax2.grid(True)

    plt.tight_layout(); plt.show()
    fig.savefig(save_as)

VGG16 Modeling

In[12]:
import numpy as np
import tensorflow as tf
from tensorflow.keras.applications.vgg16 import VGG16, preprocess_input
from tensorflow.keras.layers import (Input, Lambda, GlobalAveragePooling2D,
                                     Dropout, Dense)
from tensorflow.keras.models import Model


inputs = Input(shape=(224, 224, 3), name="input_rgb")

x = Lambda(preprocess_input, name="vgg_preproc")(inputs)

backbone = VGG16(include_top=False,
                 weights="imagenet",
                 input_tensor=x)

for layer in backbone.layers:     
    layer.trainable = False

x   = GlobalAveragePooling2D()(backbone.output)
x   = Dropout(0.50)(x)
x   = Dense(256, activation="relu")(x)
x   = Dropout(0.25)(x)
out = Dense(1, activation="sigmoid", name="pred")(x)   

model = Model(inputs, out, name="vgg16_baseline")

                           verbose=1)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import numpy as np

def plot_learning_curves(hist, save_as="mammography_vgg_learning.png"):
    acc      = hist.get('accuracy',  hist.get('acc'))
    val_acc  = hist.get('val_accuracy', hist.get('val_acc'))
    loss     = hist['loss']
    val_loss = hist['val_loss']

    epochs = range(1, len(acc) + 1)
    fig, (ax1, ax2) = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=(18, 7))
    fig.suptitle("Mammography VGG16 Baseline  Training Progress")

    ax1.plot(epochs, acc,      label='Train Acc')
    ax1.plot(epochs, val_acc,  label='Val Acc')
    ax1.set_xlabel('Epoch'); ax1.set_ylabel('Accuracy')
    ax1.legend(); ax1.grid(True)

    ax2.plot(epochs, loss,     label='Train Loss')
    ax2.plot(epochs, val_loss, label='Val Loss')
    ax2.set_xlabel('Epoch'); ax2.set_ylabel('Binary-CE Loss')
    ax2.legend(); ax2.grid(True)

    plt.tight_layout(); plt.show()
    fig.savefig(save_as)

plot_learning_curves(history_ft.history)

In[15]:
inputs = Input(shape=(224, 224, 3), name="input_rgb")

x = Lambda(preprocess_input, name="densenet_preproc")(inputs)

backbone = DenseNet121(include_top=False,
                       weights="imagenet",
                       input_tensor=x)

for layer in backbone.layers:       
    layer.trainable = False 

x   = GlobalAveragePooling2D()(backbone.output)
x   = Dropout(0.50)(x)
x   = Dense(256, activation="relu")(x)
x   = Dropout(0.25)(x)
out = Dense(1, activation="sigmoid", name="pred")(x)   

model = Model(inputs, out, name="densenet121_baseline")
